Preheat your oven to 200 degrees. Start by getting your pigs nestled in their blankets! Lay a @streaky bacon rasher{1%of 4} on a #chopping board{} and then roll the @spiced pork sausage{1%of 4} up in your bacon (see picture). Repeat with your other sausages, then pop them on a lightly greased #baking tray{}. Put them on the top shelf of your oven to cook for ~{30-35%minutes}.

> Tip: The sausage is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Whilst your pigs in blankets cook, get on with the rest of your prep. Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root. Peel and chop into ½cm cubes. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}, cut in half lengthways and slice into half moon shapes. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Put your onion in a #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle}. Cook for ~{5%minutes} until soft, then add your courgette along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{a grind}. Cook for ~{3%minutes} more. Add your garlic and @ground cumin{1.5}, stir together, then add the @red split lentils{50%g} and @chopped tomatoes{1} along with the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Refill your tin(s) half full with water and add this as well.

Bring your mixture to a gentle simmer and cook for ~{20%minutes} until your lentils have softened. Stir occasionally to make sure your lentils don't burn on the bottom of the pan.

While your lentils are cooking, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped), then you can have a little rest!

When your lentil mixture has cooked for 20 mins and your lentils are soft, add the @peas{100}, stir together and pop a lid on the pan (or some #tinfoil{} if you don't have a lid). Cook for ~{5-6%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat. Taste your lentils and add more salt and black pepper if necessary.

Serve your tomatoey lentils in #bowls{} with your pigs in blankets on top and a good sprinkling of parsley. Enjoy!